SECTION 7 — SYSTEM DOCTOR (pre-flight health check)
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Run the doctor script before starting the system to catch every known failure
mode before it silently breaks a video mid-pipeline.

Location: backend/doctor.py


— Quick check (connectivity only, no model loading, ~5 seconds):

    cd backend
    python doctor.py --quick --fix


— Full check (includes all ML model loading, ~2 minutes):

    cd backend
    python doctor.py --fix


The --fix flag auto-resolves what it can:
    • Creates missing MinIO buckets (videos, frames, documents)
    • Creates the upload temp directory if missing


— What the doctor checks:

    [Config]
      Security keys — warns if placeholder SECRET_KEY / JWT_SECRET_KEY still set
      API_KEY       — warns if unauthenticated (OK for local dev)

    [Services]
      PostgreSQL    — connection reachable
      Redis         — Celery broker reachable
      Weaviate      — ready + both collections (VideoContent, Guidelines) exist
      MinIO         — connection + all 3 required buckets exist

    [DB Schema]
      FrameAnalysis       — live write test (INSERT + ROLLBACK)
                            catches NOT NULL violations before any video is processed
      TranscriptionSegment — live write test
      ComplianceReport    — live write test
      NumPy→float cast    — verifies np.float64 is safely cast before DB insert

    [Tools]
      FFmpeg        — found on PATH

    [File System]
      Upload directory — exists and writable

    [Data]
      DPDPA Guidelines — at least 1 active rule loaded in DB

    [ML Models]  (skipped with --quick)
      YOLO          — model loads without error
      OCR           — engine can read text (not in fallback mode)
      Whisper       — model loads without error
      Embeddings    — model loads, dimension correct


— How to read the output:

    OK     ✓  — check passed
    WARN   !  — non-blocking issue (system works but may have reduced coverage)
    FAIL   ✗  — blocking issue (fix before starting worker)
    FIXED  ↻  — issue was found and automatically resolved

    If any FAIL items appear, the doctor prints the exact command to fix each one.


— Recommended workflow before every session:

    Step 1 — Start Docker:
        .\start.ps1 docker

    Step 2 — Run doctor:
        cd backend
        python doctor.py --quick --fix

    Step 3 — If all green, start services:
        .\start.ps1 api
        .\start.ps1 worker

    If doctor shows FAIL items, fix them before starting the worker.
    Running the worker with a broken schema wastes processing time and produces
    0% compliance scores with no obvious error message.
